108
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:11,570
Hashimoto, I think you have a good chance. I mean it.

109
00:07:11,570 --> 00:07:14,150
Aoki, you're kind.

110
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:21,140
But I'm fine with being a bystander right now.

111
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:24,040
Since he's my first crush, I want to treasure the moment.

112
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:27,180
I understand your feelings all too well.

113
00:07:27,180 --> 00:07:29,600
Aoki, do you also have a crush?

114
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,560
What? W-Well, yes...

115
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:35,260
Aoki, you are wonderful. You'll do fine. I'm rooting for you.

116
00:07:36,610 --> 00:07:40,910
Thank you. I'll be rooting for you, too.

117
00:07:40,910 --> 00:07:44,730
Then this will be our little secret.

118
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:49,070
Okay.

119
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:51,790
- It's a promise.
- Yes.

120
00:07:51,790 --> 00:07:54,190
I vow to protect this.

121
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:58,050
Hashimoto, I will protect your happiness no matter what.

122
00:08:13,770 --> 00:08:16,790
Sorry. Did you wait long?

123
00:08:16,790 --> 00:08:18,280
Not really.

124
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,580
Please!

125
00:08:31,580 --> 00:08:33,870
- I'm sorry!
- Don't tell anyone!

126
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,620
What?

127
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:42,820
I want you to keep quiet about the eraser.

128
00:08:42,820 --> 00:08:47,250
I will. Spilling a secret doesn't benefit me.

129
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:50,460
But people might tease or it could start rumors.

130
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:54,610
As I said, it doesn't benefit me at all.

131
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:58,460
You're... a good guy.

132
00:08:58,460 --> 00:08:59,810
What?

133
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:04,080
I see.

134
00:09:04,990 --> 00:09:08,930
Your good nature is what led to love.

135
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:14,150
H-Hold on! That's not what that meant, okay?

136
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:16,580
Aoki, I didn't notice your feelings at all.

137
00:09:16,580 --> 00:09:19,740
If I've misled you, then I'll apologize.

138
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:22,290
You're so wrong!

139
00:09:22,290 --> 00:09:26,560
That's not what that eraser meant.

140
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:28,810
Then what did it mean?

141
00:09:29,590 --> 00:09:34,280
Dammit! Anyhow, just forget that ever happened.

142
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:35,930
Bye.

143
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:39,900
- Are you okay with that?
- Say what?

144
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:42,460
Well, I mean...

145
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:50,150
I don't think you have to pretend your feelings never happened.

146
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:53,370
Though I feel bad I can't accept your feelings.

147
00:09:55,420 --> 00:09:59,490
My... feelings...

148
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:09,040
Ida,

149
00:10:12,290 --> 00:10:14,100
I...

150
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:17,900
Don't cry.

151
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:21,770
I don't want to cry, either, especially not in front of you.

152
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:26,070
Either way, I can't go out with you. I'm really sorry.

153
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:32,720
- Actually, can I punch you?
- Why?

154
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:34,670
Because I feel unsatisfied.

155
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:37,670
H-Hey! Wait a second!

156
00:10:44,350 --> 00:10:49,050
I see. So that was for this guy.

157
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:51,450
Was it really okay for me to take the last one?

158
00:10:51,450 --> 00:10:55,220
Yes. I was planning on throwing it away if no one would eat it.

159
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:59,740
Seriously? That would be a waste. This is delicious, though.

160
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:01,650
Thank you.

161
00:11:03,470 --> 00:11:06,590
Handing someone a gift is so difficult, isn't it?

162
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:11,770
I was too nervous. Man, I'm such a coward.

163
00:11:11,770 --> 00:11:16,070
She actually meant to give the cake to Ida.

164
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:22,160
Regardless, ever since that day, I...

165
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:26,400
It may sound stupid, but I seriously fell in love.

166
00:11:32,090 --> 00:11:34,540
I bet you wouldn't understand that.

167
00:11:54,530 --> 00:11:55,990
Looks good, looks good.

168
00:11:55,990 --> 00:11:59,170
- Looking good.
- Good form!

169
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,200
Looking good!

170
00:12:03,210 --> 00:12:06,850
What's wrong, Ida? Stay focused.

171
00:12:06,850 --> 00:12:08,670
- Sorry, Sir.
- Get ready.

172
00:12:08,670 --> 00:12:13,790
- Get a grip!
- Stay focused.

173
00:12:13,790 --> 00:12:16,650
What's wrong, Kosuke? Is something bothering you?

174
00:12:16,650 --> 00:12:18,730
No, it's nothing.

175
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:22,760
How unusual for you to be so unfocused during practice.

176
00:12:38,570 --> 00:12:40,200
Hey!

177
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,990
Wait up!

178
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:51,640
What the hell, Ida?

179
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:55,430
Well, I wanted to ask you something.

180
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:58,460
What sort of guy is Aoki?

181
00:12:58,470 --> 00:13:00,080
Excuse me?

182
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:02,900
You're friends with Aoki, right?

183
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:07,570
I am, but... why?

184
00:13:07,570 --> 00:13:09,740
You see...

185
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:13,620
he's exactly as he looks.

186
00:13:14,220 --> 00:13:18,270
He's an idiot, and he has a sweet tooth.

187
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:20,360
What about his crush?

188
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:25,690
Oh... we don't really do the whole, "romance talk" thing.

189
00:13:27,170 --> 00:13:28,760
Why?

190
00:13:28,770 --> 00:13:32,440
Do you want blackmail material? Are you two arguing?

191
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:37,410
No, I just didn't know him really well

192
00:13:37,410 --> 00:13:39,720
and hurt his feelings.

193
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:45,780
I don't really get it, but do you want me to tell him

194
00:13:45,780 --> 00:13:48,160
that you totally reflected on your actions?

195
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:51,920
No. I don't want to trouble you. Plus,

196
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:54,920
I can't get my feelings across unless I say it in person.

197
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:57,300
I don't want to settle this half-heartedly.

198
00:13:57,300 --> 00:14:00,420
See you tomorrow. Sorry to stop you.

199
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:09,600
Ida is...

200
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:15,420
a ridiculously good guy.

201
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:24,060
That's hilarious! You tripped in the bath and punched the floor? You're a real idiot.

202
00:14:24,060 --> 00:14:26,450
Yes, yes, I am an idiot.

203
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:29,790
- Nothing I didn't know.
- The hell?

204
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:32,890
Good morning.

205
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:35,820
- Hashimoto.
- Morning.

206
00:14:35,820 --> 00:14:37,870
And... Ida.

207
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:41,430
Oh? Why are the two of you together? How unusual.

208
00:14:41,430 --> 00:14:45,180
So are you two on good terms with one another?

209
00:14:45,180 --> 00:14:48,630
We had a meeting for Disciplinary Committee this morning, so it is a coincidence.

210
00:14:48,630 --> 00:14:51,800
It was merely a coincidence. Right, Ida?

211
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:54,550
What? R-Right.

212
00:14:54,550 --> 00:15:02,330
I see... your desperation to convince us otherwise, makes it even more suspicious.

213
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:07,640
What the hell! Dude, it hurts. You idiot!

214
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:11,560
I'm going to the school store. Bye!

215
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:15,240
Me too.

216
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:26,090
Aoki.

217
00:15:26,090 --> 00:15:30,840
Why did you run away? Wasn't that the perfect chance to talk to him?

218
00:15:30,850 --> 00:15:33,650
It was, but...

219
00:15:33,650 --> 00:15:38,660
I was so nervous. My heart couldn't handle it.

220
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:42,570
If I stayed any closer to him, it'd have ended badly.

221
00:15:42,570 --> 00:15:44,600
Your face pretty much said it all.

222
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:48,680
I was doing my best to act natural, you know?

223
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:54,410
Man, why can't I talk to him like I talk to you?

224
00:15:57,350 --> 00:16:00,600
Talking to you calmed my nerves.

225
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,640
Let's head on back.

226
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:12,190
Wait, Hashimoto.

227
00:16:17,230 --> 00:16:24,060
Hashimoto... there's something I want you to hear.

228
00:16:28,110 --> 00:16:33,160
W-Well... listen...

229
00:16:35,050 --> 00:16:40,110
The person... I like is...

230
00:16:46,010 --> 00:16:50,140
Is... well...

231
00:16:54,350 --> 00:16:56,180
Aoki.

232
00:16:57,690 --> 00:17:00,420
- Your hands—
- That's easy peasy!

233
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:02,880
You can tell me anything.

234
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:08,110
You've lent an ear to my woes of love, so now it's my turn to listen!

235
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,960
What? N-No, I...

236
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:13,310
I'll be here for any advice, so don't hold back!

237
00:17:13,310 --> 00:17:17,830
How heartening. Let's both do our best!

238
00:17:19,820 --> 00:17:21,150
Yes.

239
00:17:21,150 --> 00:17:24,590
Hip, hip, hooray!

240
00:17:24,590 --> 00:17:26,380
Hooray!

241
00:17:26,380 --> 00:17:28,560
Oh, we'll be late for class.

242
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:31,190
Not only she has no romantic feelings for me,

243
00:17:31,190 --> 00:17:33,290
