261
00:18:57,660 --> 00:19:01,190
What brings you here, Ida?

262
00:19:01,190 --> 00:19:03,300
I mean...

263
00:19:04,570 --> 00:19:08,240
- Is it fun to look down on me?
- I'm not looking down on you.

264
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:13,700
I came up here because I was worried you would be crying again.

265
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:16,020
Then I saw you were going to jump,

266
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:19,210
so I was terrified.

267
00:19:21,110 --> 00:19:25,590
Well... I'm sorry for scaring you.

268
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:34,440
Anyway, I'm fine now. Just leave me alone.

269
00:19:35,910 --> 00:19:38,140
No,

270
00:19:38,140 --> 00:19:40,720
I can't leave you alone.

271
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:43,980
Excuse me? Do you hear yourself?

272
00:19:43,980 --> 00:19:46,970
Trust me, I'm just as confused as you are.

273
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:52,460
I've been thinking since yesterday.

274
00:19:52,470 --> 00:19:55,570
- Since when?
- Since your confession.

275
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:02,110
Don't worry about that.

276
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:04,510
To be honest...

277
00:20:04,510 --> 00:20:08,300
I don't really understand what it means to "like" and "dislike" someone.

278
00:20:09,330 --> 00:20:13,560
Hey, how does it feel to "like" someone?

279
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:18,080
Even if you ask me...

280
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:23,450
More importantly, have you never had a crush before?

281
00:20:32,180 --> 00:20:33,390
Not once.

282
00:20:33,390 --> 00:20:35,680
For real?

283
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,270
Which means...

284
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:40,840
Me? There is no way I can.

285
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,510
I bet he likes someone else.

286
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:47,190
There is an opportunity for me.

287
00:20:47,190 --> 00:20:50,070
But you must have an ideal type at least, right?

288
00:20:50,070 --> 00:20:51,500
My ideal type?

289
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:55,030
What sort of hairstyle do you prefer? Long or short?

290
00:20:56,010 --> 00:21:01,180
This long, or this short. You must have some preference.

291
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:04,980
I guess I like short hair.

292
00:21:04,980 --> 00:21:06,950
What about height?

293
00:21:06,950 --> 00:21:12,010
Short, or tall and slender?

294
00:21:14,260 --> 00:21:16,060
I like that.

295
00:21:16,060 --> 00:21:20,350
Then what about personality? Outgoing or conservative?

296
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:23,770
If I had to choose... I prefer a conservative type.

297
00:21:24,620 --> 00:21:26,890
It's right on the mark!

298
00:21:26,890 --> 00:21:29,620
How so? You're the complete opposite.

299
00:21:29,620 --> 00:21:33,990
I guess. What else do you like?

300
00:21:33,990 --> 00:21:36,310
Someone who remains true to themselves.

301
00:21:36,310 --> 00:21:39,960
I totally get it. Someone who behaves in an unaffected manner?

302
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:42,590
What about you?

303
00:21:43,180 --> 00:21:44,880
Me?

304
00:21:46,380 --> 00:21:48,360
Well...

305
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:55,110
I like someone with a pretty smile

306
00:21:55,110 --> 00:21:58,890
and kind. Stuff like that.

307
00:22:00,180 --> 00:22:05,390
Plus, whenever we speak, it makes me super happy.

308
00:22:05,390 --> 00:22:08,430
I could only think of the conversations we had.

309
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:14,990
Before I knew it, I fell in love for no particular reason.

310
00:22:18,740 --> 00:22:23,310
You'll understand it once you fall for someone.

311
00:22:28,590 --> 00:22:32,150
Say something. You're making me feel embarrassed.

312
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:38,120
I just thought your straightforwardness was really nice.

313
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:45,480
Thanks for that.

314
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:47,780
- Hey.
- Yes?

315
00:22:47,780 --> 00:22:50,980
Can you wait a bit more for my answer?

316
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:54,120
Why? I said I'm totally fine with your rejection.

317
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:57,470
No, it's not. I want to give you an answer after I get to know you better.

318
00:22:57,470 --> 00:23:02,040
♫ I want us to fall in love. It wasn’t supposed to be this way ♫

319
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:03,780
I'll give it a serious thought. So please, wait a bit.

320
00:23:03,780 --> 00:23:06,830
♫ It also excites my innocent heart ♫

321
00:23:06,830 --> 00:23:10,710
♫ Just like a magnet, we stick together then we separate ♫

322
00:23:10,710 --> 00:23:12,350
♫ Oh my god, oh my god ♫

323
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:15,070
♫ Love isn’t easy ♫

324
00:23:15,070 --> 00:23:17,720
I'll head to the classroom first.

325
00:23:18,740 --> 00:23:23,710
♫ I’m smitten with you. You’re my sunshine ♫

326
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:28,270
Wait, what just had happened?

327
00:23:28,270 --> 00:23:31,470
What sort of twist is this?

328
00:23:31,470 --> 00:23:33,820
[Next Episode]
Amazing! What is it?

329
00:23:33,820 --> 00:23:35,320
You're an interesting guy.

330
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:38,100
Hashimoto, where's your house? I'll walk you home.
[Friendship and love, patterns that intersect—]

331
00:23:38,100 --> 00:23:40,200
Don't let it get to you.
[Will a spell be cast at the school festival?]

332
00:23:41,530 --> 00:23:42,750
Are you all right?

333
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:46,570
Is it so wrong to wish for the happiness of my crush?
[It started from misunderstanding, but how will the love turn out!?]
